        content: `You're getting an infinite loop because your \`useEffect\` hook doesn't have a dependency array. This means it runs after every single render. Since you're updating state inside the effect (\`setData\`), it causes a re-render, which triggers the effect again. \n\nTo fix this, you should provide an empty dependency array \`[]\` to the \`useEffect\` hook. This tells React to only run the effect once, after the initial render.\n\nCorrected code:\n\`\`\`javascript\nuseEffect(() => {\n  fetch('/api/data')\n    .then(res => res.json())\n    .then(setData);\n}, []); // <-- Add this empty array\n\`\`\`\n\nUsing a library like **SWR** or **React Query** is highly recommended for more complex scenarios, as they handle caching, revalidation, and error handling for you out of the box.`,
